ing using dependency resolution in a temporary directory. Maybe I could utilize Gradle within this temp area to avoid modifying the main repository. The /tmp directory seems to be a good option for that. However, I'll also need artifact information, so I'll look into using curl to access Maven Central. It's crucial to keep everything organized and contained in this temporary setup while I sort out the dependencies. Sounds like a plan!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_FgXBgbUm5mx2mzwZO9l7iRo0|fc_068947734e33e0d7016a42b88dc8c081948cc3690c41a9ef08", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nimport urllib.request\nurl='https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/net/sf/ehcache/ehcache-core/2.5.0/ehcache-core-2.5.0.pom'\ntry:\n    print(urllib.request.urlopen(url, timeout=20).read().decode()[:20000])\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print('ERR', repr(e))\nPY", "timeout": 30}}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_VQL6lh8A18dUV7tC22tnuvCy|fc_068947734e33e0d7016a42b88dc8d48194b6d6496e62f1e191", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nimport urllib.request\nfor url in ['https://www.ehcache.org/documentation/2.8/get-started/getting-started.html','https://www.ehcache.org/documentation/2.8/apis/cache-usage.html','https://www.ehcache.org/documentation/2.8/apis/transactions.html']:\n    try:\n        data=urllib.request.urlopen(url, timeout=15).read().decode(errors='ignore')\n        print('\\nURL', url, 'LEN', len(data))\n        print(data[:1000])\n    except Exception as e: print('ERR', url, repr(e))\nPY", "timeout": 45}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 392, "output": 334, "cacheRead": 15872, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 16598, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782757513203, "responseId": "resp_068947734e33e0d7016a42b889ad108194a317faea2cb307e8"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_