n 2.5.0 introduces memory-based cache sizing, I might use the SizeOf engine and embedded agent. I also need to consider JVM shared usage and temporary projects. To avoid modifying the repo, a local mini Gradle project might be best. I’ll also need to ensure my temp directory isn't full to prevent any Gradle failures.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Inspecting POM resolution**\\n\\nI need to look into the POM resolution, focusing on compiling SLF4J and checking provided dependencies like JTA, Hibernate, and Servlet. I wonder if the existing Gradle is bringing in JTA. The native image command shows metadata for javax.transaction/jta due to the build.gradle file, but no metadata for btm/geronimo, which might be omitted. Existing tests use btm, and with the \\\"deterministic_setup,\\\" I can apply dependencies beforehand. If generated tests try to use transaction APIs, they'll fail since JDK 17+ doesn’t include javax.transaction. So, I need to address existing library updates to resolve run failures.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating test coverage needs**\\n\\nI see that with version 2.4.4, the existing test coverage already includes transaction classes. To maintain that coverage and avoid failures, I’ll need JTA and BTM. However, the user suggests I should \\\"choose no_action\\\" unless there's solid evidence that extra setup is necessary. We do have concrete evidence from the artifacts and documentation regarding transactions, but perhaps additional steps are only necessary if we want meaningful coverage for transaction manager lookups. Normally, Ehcache is used as a standalone without Docker, which complicates the optional Maven dependencies.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_dqomWoFHENuazGWaBlKE9Unz|fc_068947734e33e0d7016a42b8c1863881949fe2fe473adcc4aa", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nimport urllib.request, re\nfor coord,path in [('btm-2.1.4','https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/codehaus/btm/btm/2.1.4/btm-2.1.4.pom'),('btm-2.0.1','https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/codehaus/btm/btm/2.0.1/btm-2.0.1.pom')]:\n  print('---',coord)\n  data=urllib.request.urlopen(path, timeout=20).read().decode()\n  for m in re.finditer(r'<dependency>.*?</dependency>', data, re.S):\n    dep=m.group(0)\n    if any(x in dep for x in ['jms','transaction','geronimo','slf4j']): print(dep.strip())\nPY", "timeout": 30}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1879, "output": 956, "cacheRead": 33792, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 36627, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782757556157, "responseId": "resp_068947734e33e0d7016a42b8b4d81481949b5088e79a4caed6"}}
